{# The household occupant, embodying felt comfort. The `tier` prop
   (cold | cool | warm | hot, from HouseSceneView::comfortState) selects one of
   four hand-designed full-body SVGs — one whole character per state, so there
   is no CSS layer toggling: the component just includes the right file. The
   `occupant--{{ tier }}` class stays as a semantic hook (future per-state
   ambience), not a visibility switch.

   A bit of life: the inner `.occupant-life` group takes a per-day position keyed
   by `pose` — a deterministic 0..6 (day number % 7), each a distinct, non-linear
   horizontal spot + facing (scene.css). No randomness (the sim stays
   seeded/replayable). The base placement transform stays on the OUTER group, so
   the CSS transform on `.occupant-life` never fights it. #}
{% props tier = 'warm', pose = 0 %}
<g class="occupant occupant--{{ tier }}"{{ attributes }}>
    <g class="occupant-life occupant-life--p{{ pose }}">{{ include('game/scene/assets/occupant-' ~ tier ~ '.svg') }}</g>
</g>
